WEBVTT

00:09.509 --> 00:11.602
Hey, Nat,
someone keeps taking down

00:11.644 --> 00:13.544
my Roger Corman Film Festival
posters.

00:13.580 --> 00:15.639
It was me.
I figured four was enough.

00:15.682 --> 00:16.910
Never enough!

00:16.950 --> 00:18.349
Come on, I'm doing
this for course credit

00:18.385 --> 00:20.080
in Film Theory,
and promotion counts.

00:20.120 --> 00:21.951
Not to mention the king himself,

00:21.988 --> 00:24.320
the pope of pulp is coming
here to bless the event.

00:24.357 --> 00:27.190
Oh. Excuse me if I don't
kiss his ring.

00:27.227 --> 00:28.455
What's the matter?

00:28.495 --> 00:30.190
Too lowbrow for you.

00:30.230 --> 00:31.822
Check out some of these movies...
look at this.

00:31.865 --> 00:34.993
Machine Gun Kelly,
Swamp Woman. The Undead.

00:35.101 --> 00:36.227
Very impressive, Steve.

00:38.071 --> 00:40.335
Everybody's a critic.

00:44.444 --> 00:46.378
Hotel stationery.

00:46.413 --> 00:47.937
Let me guess, your father.

00:47.981 --> 00:49.005
He's coming in tomorrow.

00:49.115 --> 00:50.412
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

00:50.450 --> 00:53.283
- I just got the letter today.
- Typical.

00:53.319 --> 00:55.014
What are you going
to do about it?

00:55.055 --> 00:56.113
I don't know.

00:56.156 --> 00:57.783
He wants me to meet him
at the airport.

00:57.824 --> 01:00.486
Probably so he'll have someone
to talk to during his layover.

01:00.527 --> 01:02.518
That's not it.

01:02.562 --> 01:03.620
He's coming here to stay.

01:03.663 --> 01:04.959
For how long?

01:04.998 --> 01:06.966
He says he's moving here.

01:07.067 --> 01:08.694
And you believe him?

01:08.735 --> 01:10.293
Why shouldn't I?

01:10.336 --> 01:12.133
Let me see...

01:12.172 --> 01:14.072
I could give you
21 years of reasons.

01:14.107 --> 01:17.133
Why are you always this way
when it comes to him?

01:17.177 --> 01:19.168
Because he's done nothing
but disappoint you

01:19.212 --> 01:20.509
since the day you were born.

01:20.547 --> 01:21.775
That is not true.

01:21.815 --> 01:24.807
Honey, you have always worn
rose-colored glasses

01:24.851 --> 01:26.148
when it comes to your father.

01:26.186 --> 01:27.983
I just don't want you
to be hurt again.

01:28.021 --> 01:30.148
Mom, he came to my graduation.
I didn't even ask him.

01:30.190 --> 01:32.090
Well, when you have
such low expectations,

01:32.125 --> 01:33.649
I guess any crumb is a meal.

01:33.693 --> 01:36.992
He's taken good care of me.

01:37.063 --> 01:38.587
And let's face it,

01:38.631 --> 01:41.498
you haven't exactly been
the model mother or wife.

01:41.534 --> 01:45.630
Well, if you mean by
"taking good care of you,"

01:45.672 --> 01:47.264
that you always had plenty
of money, fine.

01:47.307 --> 01:50.037
Just don't come crying to me
when he breaks your heart again.

